  "prompt": "What should I do with someone who talks behind my back and is a fake friend?",
  "response": "Dealing with someone who talks behind your back and isn\u2019t a genuine friend can be challenging. Here are some steps you can take to address the situation:\n\n1. **Reflect on the Situation**: Take some time to consider the behavior you\u2019ve noticed. Is it a pattern, or was it an isolated incident? Understanding the context can help you decide how to respond.\n\n2. **Gather Evidence**: If you\u2019re comfortable, talk to mutual friends to see if they\u2019ve noticed similar behavior. This can help you confirm what\u2019s been happening.\n\n3. **Confront Gently**: If you feel safe and ready, consider directly addressing the issue with the person. Choose a private setting and express your feelings honestly without being confrontational. Use \"I\" statements to communicate how their behavior affects you.\n\n4. **Set Boundaries**: If the person continues to be a fake friend after your conversation, it may be necessary to set boundaries. Decide how much time and energy you want to invest in the relationship moving forward.\n\n5. **Seek Support**: Talk to trusted friends or family about your feelings. They can offer perspective, support, and advice on how to handle the situation.\n\n6. **Focus on Positive Relationships**: Invest your time and energy in friendships that are supportive and fulfilling. Surrounding yourself with genuine people can help you heal from the negative experience.\n\n7. **Consider Letting Go**: If the person continues to be toxic, it might be healthiest to distance yourself from them. Prioritize relationships that bring you joy and support.\n\n8. **Practice Self-care**: Take care of your emotional well-being. Engage in activities that make you happy, stress-relief practices, or hobbies to help you move past the situation.\n\nRemember that you deserve to have friends who uplift and support you, and it\u2019s okay to distance yourself from those who don\u2019t.",
